PyPy version throws exception when timezone is not FixedTimezone while C version silently formats it as +00:00

**Python**

``` python
    offset = 0
    sign = '+'

    if date_time.tzinfo is not None:
        if date_time.tzinfo.__class__ is not TZFixedOffset:
            # TODO: Support all tzinfo subclasses by calling utcoffset()
            raise ValueError('Only TZFixedOffset supported.')
        offset = date_time.tzinfo.offset
```

**C**

``` c
 int offset = 0;

    // TODO: Support all tzinfo subclasses by calling utcoffset()
    if (datetime_obj->hastzinfo) {
        if (Py_TYPE(datetime_obj->tzinfo) == &FixedOffset_type) {
            FixedOffset *tzinfo = (FixedOffset *)datetime_obj->tzinfo;
            offset = tzinfo->offset;
        }
    }
```
